  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nOfficial docker image from Docker Hub, stable tag\r\n\r\ngit_branch=stable git_tag=v2022.01.02 git_commit=ea9ad474467af7a924063a50a6c9f9c82ad5d1d9\r\n\r\nOS & Version:\r\nUnraid 6.9.2\r\n\r\n```\r\nerigon --chain goerli --private.api.addr=0.0.0.0:9090\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nrpcdaemon --datadir=/home/erigon/.local/share/erigon --private.api.addr=127.0.0.1:9090 --txpool.api.addr=127.0.0.1:9090 --http.api=eth,erigon,web3,net,debug,trace,txpool --http.addr=0.0.0.0 --http.vhosts=* --http.corsdomain=*\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\n`eth_sendRawTransaction` type 2 transaction is parsed correctly \r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nTransaction is submitted, but can't be parsed, making txpool stuck\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nSubmit a type 2 transaction using `eth_sendRawTransaction`\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\ntoday at 16:10:01[WARN] [01-23|16:10:01.166] OnNewTx rpc filters, unprocessable payload err=EOF data=02\r\ntoday at 16:10:01[INFO] [01-23|16:10:01.166] Submitted transaction hash=0x123 from=0x123 nonce=1234 recipient=0x123 value=0x0\r\n````\r\n\r\nThen, on restart:\r\n```\r\nError: pool not started yet\r\n```\r\n\r\nSame type 2 transaction was working correctly on latest Erigon version ~December 6.\r\nWould be happy to test further if you need more info.\r\n\r\nI deleted `txpool` folder and changed the transaction to type 1 to temporarily fix the issue.",
